Government Decision: - The 505 temporary posts created for the 35 constituent office under the Directorate General of Police, Maharashtra State, Mumbai have been abolished by the Government Decision in Reference No. 9. 01.03.2024 that is. The extension has been granted subject to the condition given by the Department of Finance up to 31.08.2024.

The above mentioned Reference No. 3 by the decision of the Government of the Finance Department here. 01.09.2024 that is. The power to extend temporary posts up to 28.02.2025 has been delegated to the Ministries / Administrative Departments. The above Reference No. According to the letter 2B, 505 temporary posts have been created for the 35 constituent offices under the Director General of Police, Maharashtra State, Mumbai. A proposal has been submitted for further extension from 01.09.2024. Accordingly, 505 temporary posts in 35 constituent offices under the Directorate General of Police, Maharashtra State, Mumbai, notified in the co-signer accompanying this Government decision, have been given. 01.09.2024 that is. The Government is approving the extension up to 28.02.2025 subject to the following conditions.
1) None of the posts proposed is vacant for more than six months and the temporary posts have been filled up subject to the terms and conditions for which they have been approved.

2) Department of Finance, Government Decision No. Designation-2016 / Q. 08/16 APC, D. The terms and conditions prescribed under the 06.09.2024 shall be followed scrupulously and shall be dealt with accordingly.

3) In the meantime, action should be taken to review the sanctioned posts before the establishment of your office and determine the revised figure. Accordingly, further action regarding inclusion of temporary posts in the revised structure is to be taken by all the administrative departments with immediate effect. Also, the extension of temporary posts should be treated as the last one, after which the period for fixing the revised figure will not be extended.

Accordingly, the concerned should be instructed to take immediate action by planning to immediately submit a proposal for a revised framework to the Finance Department. As the revised pattern has not been finalised, no further extension of temporary posts has been granted to the officers / staff.
If the question of salary and allowances arises, it will be the responsibility of the Director General of Police, Maharashtra State, Mumbai.

The expenditure in this case shall be met from the grant sanctioned under the head "Home Department, Demand No: B-1" 2055-Police- (00) 109 District Police (00) (01) District Police Force (01) Salary. "

3. The said Government Decision Finance Department, Government Decision No. Posts-2016 / P.S.No.08 / 16 / A.P.C., D. Issuance is being done in accordance with the powers conferred on the Ministries / Administrative Departments under 06.09.2024.
